==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek ''[[ἀήρ]]'', through Latin ''[[aero-]]'', combining form for '''air''' + Greek ''[[πλάνης]]'' planis, a wanderer

===Alternative spellings===
*''(UK):'' [[aeroplane]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-airplane.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{US}} A powered [[aircraft]] with fixed [[wing]]s used for [[transportation]] of humans and goods; for [[amusement]] or [[entertainment]]; and in [[warfare]].  An [[aeroplane]].

